korean:
  title: 사 성지 기거 표
  author: 이제현
  language: kor
  text: 어린 나이에 북으로 올라와서 3년 동안 특별히 사랑을 받았으며 뼈에 새겨 동으로 돌아갔으니 하루인들 어찌 축수하기를 잊으오리까.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0400_010_0340&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Memorial of Gratitude for Royal Favor
  author: Lee Ge-hyeon
  language: eng
  text: |-
    In my youth I journeyed north,
    Three years blessed with uncommon grace—
    Your favor carved into my very bones.
    Now homeward bound to the east,
    How could a single day erase
    My vow to remember your benevolence?
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: This work is a formal memorial (표, 'pyo') expressing gratitude to the royal court, likely written upon Lee Ge-hyeon's return to Korea after serving at the Yuan court in the north.
  - key: ''
    value: The contrast between 'north' (Yuan court) and 'east' (Korea/Goryeo) reflects the geopolitical positioning of the period when Korea maintained tributary relations with the Yuan Dynasty.
